text: Waddikee is a locality on Eyre Peninsula in South Australia. It is on the Eyre Peninsula Railway southwest of Kimba. The former railway stations of Waddikee and Caralue are both in the current locality of Waddikee. Caralue siding opened in 1915. Waddikee siding opened in 1921. The current locality of Caralue is north and west of these stations. The stations had government towns surveyed around them in 1926 and 1927. ==References== Category:Towns in South Australia
